'''Commentary''' may refer to:

*[[Sports commentary|Play-by-play]] commentary, describing sporting events on TV or radio
**[[Color commentator|colour commentary]], supplementing play-by-play commentary with talk not directly about play
*Commentary or narration, the words in a [[documentary film]]
*[[Commentary (magazine)|''Commentary'' (magazine)]], a US public affairs journal, founded in 1945 and formerly published by the American Jewish Committee
*The [[audio commentary|audio commentary track for DVDs]], an additional audio track that plays in real time with video and comments on the video
*[[Political criticism|Political commentary]], criticism that is specific of or relevant to politics
*A literary commentary, or [[close reading]]
*[[Literary criticism]], the study, evaluation, and interpretation of literature
*A [[Commentary (philology)|philological commentary]], a line-by-line or even word-by-word explication
*[[Exegesis|Bible commentary]], a critical explanation or interpretation of a text, especially a religious text
**[[List of biblical commentaries]]
**[[Jewish commentaries on the Bible]]
*In Theravada Buddhism commentaries on the Pali Canon are known as ''[[atthakatha]]''
*Informed [[criticism]]
*Topics covered by a [[discussion group]]
*Misspelling of [[Commentry]], a place in France
*''Commentaries'' is a work attributed to [[Taautus]]
*A number of works by or attributed to Julius Caesar, most notably:
**''[[Commentarii de Bello Gallico]]'', &quot;Commentaries on the Gallic War&quot;
**''[[Commentarii de Bello Civili]]'', &quot;Commentaries on the Civil War&quot;
*The ''[[Commentaries on the Laws of England]]'', a 1769 treatise on law
*Commentary! The Musical, the musical commentary accompanying ''[[Dr. Horrible's Sing-Along Blog]]''
*[[In-Theater Audio Commentary]], viewing a film in a theater while listening to commentary on a portable audio player

