  <page>
    <title>Chinese</title>
    <id>5347</id>
    <revision>
      <id>431124749</id>
      <timestamp>2011-05-27T04:04:27Z</timestamp>
      <contributor>
        <ip>71.125.131.226</ip>
      </contributor>
      <comment>;pwhfbFHGQPOUERHGURGQHGQHQTHHTRQRHT</comment>
      <text xml:space="preserve">{{pp-move-indef}}
{{Wiktionary}}
'''Chinese''' refers to anything pertaining to the Chinese people. 

* [[Chinese people]], people of Chinese nationality, or one of several Chinese ethnicities
** ''[[Zhonghua minzu]]'', the supra-ethnic Chinese nationality
** [[Han Chinese]], the dominant ethnic group in [[People's Republic of China|mainland China]], [[Republic of China|Taiwan]] and [[Singapore]]
** [[Ethnic minorities in China]], the non-Han Chinese population in [[People's Republic of China|mainland China]] and [[Republic of China|Taiwan]]
** [[Overseas Chinese]], people of Chinese ancestry who live outside [[People's Republic of China|mainland China]] and [[Republic of China|Taiwan]]

* [[Chinese language]], a language or language family that forms part of the Sino-Tibetan family of languages
** [[Standard Chinese]], the standard form of the Chinese language and most commonly taught as a foreign language. It is also an official spoken form in [[People's Republic of China|maiyjueyuetyuy5lwhkjydlp
qwenland China]] and [[Republic of China|Taiwan]], and the predominantly Chinese [[Singapore]].
** [[Cantonese]], often officially referred to as &quot;Chinese&quot; in the special administrative regions of [[Hong Kong]] and [[Macau]] in the People's Republic of China
** other [[varieties of Chinese]]

* [[Written Chinese]], the writing system of China. ''See also'' [[Chinese character]] (Hanzi)
** [[Traditional Chinese characters]], officially used in [[Taiwan]], [[Hong Kong]] and [[Macau]], and used by many Overseas Chinese communities.
** [[Simplified Chinese characters]], officially used in [[Mainland China]], [[Singapore]] and [[Malaysia]]fuvk uuh, and used in some [[Overseas Chinese]] communities.
** [[Romanization of Chinese]], with several systems
** [[Hanja]] Chinese characters used in writing [[Korean language]]
** [[Kanji]] Chinese characters used in writing [[Japanese language]]

* [[Chinese cuisine]], styles of cooking originating from China

==See also==
* [[Culture of China]], including:
** [[Chinese art]]
** [[Chinese folklore]]
** [[Chinese literature]]
** [[Chinese mythology]]
** [[Chinese poetry]]
** [[History of China]]
** [[Music of China]], including [[C-pop]]
** [[Chinese Dance]]
* [[Chinese name]]

'''Chinese''' may also used as a modifier for Western activities and items that are most likely not of Chinese origin, such as:
*[[Chinese auction]]
*[[Chinese checkers]]
*[[Chinese fire drill]]
*[[Chinese jump rope]]
*[[Chinese poker]]
*[[Chinese whispers]]
*[[Chinese pie]] (Pâté chinois)
 
For the etymology of the word '''Chinese''', see [[Names of China]].

